cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning, specifically on RGB-D scene recognition using deep learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture and training approach for learning effective depth-specific features, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper addresses the limitations of RGB-D data, which could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper introduces a new RGB-D video dataset and proposes a video recognition architecture, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
